[src:gcc-internals/optimizing-compiler] Unswitching moves a conditional from inside a loop to outside the loop by duplicating the loop's body inside each of the if and else clauses of the conditional.
[src:gcc-internals/optimizing-compiler] The loop is restructured in such a way that work done in an iteration is split into several parts and done over several iterations.
